text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus rhomboidea, commonly known as the diamond gum, is a tree that is native to Western Australia.The tree typically grows to a height of 8 to 10 metres (26 to 33 ft) in height. It is found on rises in the Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia between Dundas and Yilgarn where in grows in gravelly-sandy soils.
